    public interface FundsTracker
extends com.guidewire.bc.domain.fundstracking.gen.FundsTrackerStubI
    A FundsTracker tracks allotments of funds from a FundsSource or allotments of funds to a FundsUse.

      • isTrackingReversal

        boolean isTrackingReversal()
        Returns whether this tracker is tracking a reversal. For example, the fundsSourceTracker which is tracking a DirectBillMoneyReceived is not tracking a reversal, but the fundsUseTracker which tracks the reversal of that DirectBillMoneyReceived is tracking a reversal. The fundsUseTracker which is tracking a Disbursement is not tracking a reversal, but the fundsSourceTracker which tracks the reversal of that Disbursement is tracking a reversal.
        Returns:
        whether this tracker is tracking a reversal.

      • getTrackerOfReversedEntity

        FundsTracker getTrackerOfReversedEntity()
        If this tracker is tracking a reversal, returns the tracker that tracks the reversed entity. Returns null if this tracker is not tracking a reversal.

      • unallotFunds

        void unallotFunds()
        Unallots all of the allotments for this fund tracker. Makes this fund tracker be fully unallotted. This decreases the amount allotted for all of the fund trackers that were allotted to or from this tracker.
